   GFF AI PTE LTD. does not store client credentials or live processing variables on third-party analytical engines. This architecture allows audit groups and risk compliance teams to inspect execution states without creating a single vector of entry.\n514 |               </p>\n515 |             </div>\n516 | \n517 |             {/* Sandbox Simulation Notice */}\n518 |             <div className=\"p-5 rounded-xl border border-[#009DFF]/20 bg-[#009DFF]/5 text-[#009DFF] space-y-2 font-sans\">\n519 |               <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n520 |                 <ShieldAlert className=\"w-5 h-5 shrink-0 text-[#009DFF]\" />\n521 |                 <h4 className=\"text-[13px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-white font-mono\">PREVIEW GATEWAY SIMULATION NOTICE</h4>\n522 |               </div>\n523 |               <p className=\"text-[11.5px] leading-relaxed text-white/70 font-light\">\n524 |                 <strong>Authentication & Database States are Localized Sandbox Previews.</strong> To permit complete corporate evaluations of GFF AI's suite interfaces, all database reads, live milestones, invoice generation, support triage, and model parameters operate within a client-side sandbox environment. No actual production connections or API requests are performed during this executive walkthrough.\n525 |               </p>\n526 |             </div>\n527 | \n528 |             <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 pt-2 font-sans\">\n529 |               <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2.5\">\n530 |                 <CheckSquare className=\"w-4 h-4 text-emerald-400 shrink-0\" />\n531 |                 <span className=\"text-[12.5px] text-white/80 font-light\">No credentials cached on disk</span>\n532 |               </div>\n533 |               <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2.5\">\n534 |                 <CheckSquare className=\"w-4 h-4 text-emerald-400 shrink-0\" />\n535 |                 <span className=\"text-[12.5px] text-white/80 font-light\">Safe compliance simulation</span>\n536 |               </div>\n537 |             </div>\n538 |           </div>\n539 | \n540 |         </div>\n541 |       </section>\n542 | \n543 |       {/* 5. COMPLIANCE BENTO GRID */}\n544 |       <section className=\"relative w-full px-6 lg:px-16 py-20 lg:py-24\">\n545 |         <div className=\"max-w-[1795px] mx-auto space-y-12\">\n546 |           <div className=\"text-center space-y-4\">\n547 |             <span className=\"text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.15em] text-[#009DFF] uppercase\">\n548 |               Security Frameworks\n549 |             </span>\n550 |             <h2 className=\"text-[28px] sm:text-[40px] font-bold text-white tracking-tight\">\n551 |               Cryptographically Isolated Deliverables\n552 |             </h2>\n553 |             <p className=\"text-[14px] sm:text-[16px] text-white/60 font-light max-w-[620px] mx-auto font-sans\">\n554 |               Our platform adheres strictly to elite secure software execution practices. We focus on transparent architecture over opaque, unverified badges.\n555 |             </p>\n556 |           </div>\n557 | \n558 |           <BentoGrid>\n559 |             <BentoCard\n560 |               title=\"Secure handshakes isolate live systems\"\n561 |               description=\"Sovereign presentation paths ensure that visual audits are Decoupled. Handshake protocols verify sessions using transient single-use key enclaves.\"\n562 |               badge=\"HANDSHAKE GATEWAY\"\n563 |               icon={<Fingerprint className=\"w-5 h-5 text-[#009DFF]\" />}\n564 |               glowColor=\"blue\"\n565 |               metric={{ value: \"0x7FFA\", label: \"HANDSHAKE SECURITY LEVEL\" }}\n566 |             />\n567 |             <BentoCard\n568 |               title=\"eBPF OS kernel telemetry\"\n569 |               description=\"Deep process tracking and automated risk policies are evaluated at the hardware core, eliminating runtime container leaks or out-of-bounds requests.\"\n570 |               badge=\"TELEMETRY LAYER\"\n571 |               icon={<Cpu className=\"w-5 h-5 text-[#E4000F]\" />}\n572 |               glowColor=\"red\"\n573 |               metric={{ value: \"eBPF\", label: \"KERNEL ISOLATION PROTOCOL\" }}\n574 |             />\n575 |             <BentoCard\n576 |               title=\"Transient database boundaries\"\n577 |               description=\"No analytical or administrative user secrets are stored on general presentation servers. Database instances are fully sandboxed and transient.\"\n578 |               badge=\"DATA SOVEREIGNTY\"\n579 |               icon={<Database className=\"w-5 h-5 text-purple-400\" />}\n580 |               glowColor=\"purple\"\n581 |               metric={{ value: \"AES-256\", label: \"ENVELOPED ENCRYPTION\" }}\n582 |             />\n583 |           </BentoGrid>\n584 |         </div>\n585 |       </section>\n586 | \n587 |       {/* 6. PREMIUM CALL TO ACTION */}\n588 |       <div className=\"max-w-[1795px] mx-auto px-6 lg:px-16 py-16\">\n589 |         <div className=\"w-full rounded-[24px] border border-white/5 bg-gradient-to-br from-[#0c0c0f] to-[#040405] p-8 sm:p-12 lg:p-16 relative overflow-hidden group text-center space-y-6\">\n590 |           <div className=\"absolute top-0 left-1/4 w-80 h-80 rounded-full bg-[#009DFF]/5 blur-[100px] pointer-events-none\" />\n591 |           <div className=\"absolute bottom-0 right-1/4 w-80 h-80 rounded-full bg-[#E4000F]/3 blur-[100px] pointer-events-none\" />\n592 |           \n593 |           <span className=\"inline-flex px-3 py-1 text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.12em] text-[#009DFF] border border-[#009DFF]/25 bg-[#009DFF]/5 rounded-full uppercase\">\n594 |             AUDIT ENCLAVE ACCESS\n595 |           </span>\n596 | \n597 |           <h2 className=\"text-[32px] sm:text-[46px] lg:text-[54px] font-bold text-white tracking-tight leading-none max-w-[800px] mx-auto\">\n598 |             Ready to Begin Sovereign Simulation?\n599 |           </h2>\